Onthatile Ribane, who died after falling into a sewage drain in the North West, was laid to rest on Thursday. The 4-year-old went missing in the Motsoseng Village in Mahikeng on Sunday. JOHANNESBURG - Onthatile Ribane, who died after falling into a sewage drain in the North West, was laid to rest on Thursday. The 4-year-old went missing in the Motsoseng Village in Mahikeng on Sunday. He had been playing at a nearby school with his friends when tragedy struck. READ: Too late to save him: Father of drowned boy (4) His body was found later that evening. Police have opened an inquest docket to determine the cause of death. But his family says there are many unanswered questions. The provinces Education department is also investigating the incident.